The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Loose Change
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     LOOSE CHANGE
                              
	 Citibank has launched Citibank Protect amp; Grow, a fixed deposit product with the option to channel the interest earned into mutual funds. Customers will be able to choose any combination of a maximum of four open-ended mutual funds from among those distributed by Citibank. The product offering is available for a minimum deposit of Rs 15 lakh for a minimum tenure of one year.                             
	 ICICI Prudential Life has launched ICICI Pru Pure Protect, a term insurance product. It is available in two variants, ICICI Pru Pure Protect Classic for sum assured of up to Rs 25,00,000 and ICICI Pru Pure Protect Elite for sum assured of Rs 25,00,000 and above. The term assurance policy aims at providing insurance at the lowest rates in the market with premium starting from Rs 2,400 per annum.                             
	 Benchmark Mutual Fund has launched Benchmark S amp;P CNX 500 Fund, an open-ended equity index fund. The fund will replicate its stated benchmark, S amp;P CNX 500. The fund will have at least 90 per cent exposure in the stocks of its chosen index. If it is not able to buy a stock that is stated in the index, it can have exposure in its derivatives instruments up to 10 per cent. The new fund offer will close on December 15.                                                                                                                             
